Installation
------------
1. Install node.js and MongoDB (on Debian/Ubuntu: "apt-get install nodejs mongodb").
2. Run "npm i" in project root to install dependencies. ("sudo npm i" can be required, depending on node.js installation)
4. Configure application (see config.js)
5. Check if tests passing "./app.js test" or "node app.js test" 
6. Run application "./app.js" or "node app.js"

